{
  "texts": [
    "FL was first introduced by McMahan (McMahan et al. 2017) and refers to a technique that allows the building of data-driven models using distributed data without the need to store them centrally.",
    "There are scenarios in which it is beneficial or even mandatory to isolate different subsets of the training data from each other.",
    "The farthest extent of this is when a model needs to be trained on datasets that each live on different machines or clusters and may under no circumstance be co-located or even moved (Wen et al. 2023).",
    "The FL architecture includes different steps in which communication between a central server and different clients is established.",
    "In this sense, this communication should be encrypted."
  ]
}